premise_source_doc_sentence: There are no standardized names for shades of brown ; the same shade may have different names on different color lists , and sometimes the one name  (  such as beige or puce  )  can refer to several very different colors .
The edge-coloring problem asks whether it is possible to color the edges of a given graph using at most different colors , for a given value of , or with the fewest possible colors .
Diamond also has relatively high optical dispersion  (  ability to disperse light of different colors  )  .
In the RGB color model used to create all the colors on computer and television screens , brown is made by combining red and green light at different intensities .
The X11 color list of web colors lists seventeen different shades of brown , but the complete list of browns is much longer .
